Flynne helps Oona to find Mossy, and proves she can be a friendly fox.
Oona and Baba search for soft bedding for their burrow.
Happy has some very big feelings when Frankie meets a bee in his garden.
Featherwand: Bluey and Mum are off to Chloe's party and Bingo isn't invited. When a passing cockatoo drops a feather, Bingo has an idea for a new game called 'Featherwand'.
Osawldobias: Oswaldo really doesn't want to do his chores. He disguises Tobias to fool his mum.
Role-Playing: It's Oswaldo's birthday! And Leia has planned a quest around the neighbourhood for him.
When Daniel and his friends are making puppets at the library, they find out that making a plan can help them put on a grr-ific puppet show!
Kenny Keeps His Cool: Whilst playing hide and seek, Kenny enters a cave he had never seen before and falls into a hole. He soon finds himself in a dark forest without sunlight.
Dee encourages a friend to say 'n', and we go on an adventure around the sound. We see a nest, some noses and a net, and watch some newts eat noodles at night!
Glitch creates big trouble with a little pyramid when he and the Go Jetters visit Egypt.
Preston left an egg sandwich out too long, and now it's explosively stinking up the whole town. Mojo and Bo need to evacuate everyone in Swoppiton before the eggy stinkplosion!
Everybody feels grumpy sometimes, especially Whizz when she doesn't get enough sleep! There's only one thing to do, the Sunshine Spread!
Poor Bellie sprains his paw and can't play with Whizz or the Forest Kids. When they make him a special present, he realises just how much he is loved.

programmes.show_name: Lex and Plu Space Taxi Drivers
programmes.show_description: The Unburdened Life: Lex and Plu have to deliver the migratory snail Dmitrian to Planet Oceania-7 and earn a positive passenger review so they don't lose their taxi license.
Holiday Blues: Just before the holidays, Pigeon Post seems uncharacteristically glum. Odo and Doodle set about trying to figure out why and help Pigeon Post back to being cheerful once again.
Flying Fox: Odo and Doodle teach Reggie the fox how to fly.
Sonia tries her best to keep still during play time and along with all the family she learns the benefits of taking a break. (SL)
Hugo and Sonia discover their cookies have been eaten and when they follow the clues, they discover something even sweeter (SL)
Bean Sundae Shoe: Fuzzy Yellow's beanbag chair has been stolen. Fuzzy Yellow first suspects Marzipan, but when they both realise that Caviar is the culprit, they track Caviar down. (SL)

Oona and Baba search for soft bedding for their burrow.
Happy has some very big feelings when Frankie meets a bee in his garden.
Band for a Stand: Helping Hand builds a bandstand so Mae-Mae decides to form a band with her friends.
Henry meets an old Grandfather Clock. He is moving house today but unfortunately the delivery truck has left without him. Henry becomes a Delivery man for the day.
Museum: MeStan gives the local children a tour of the museum, which inspires them all to make their own interactive exhibition about their town and all the characters that live there.
House: Mayor Myrtle urgently needs a spare bed for an important visitor. 'Can Do' says Stanley, but the new bed won't fit inside Myrtle's house.

programmes.show_name: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go
programmes.show_description: Sameroo: A younger Thomas the Tank Engine goes on adventures with all of his friends as they work on the island of Sodor.
A washed-up ribbon inspires Lily to teach Salty how to fly a kite. After one-too-many disasters, Lily learns that Salty is more confident at sea and comes up with a plan to help.
Salty is challenged to a dance-off by Lord Stag at the Driftwood Bay ceilidh, so Lily and her friends help him to get his legs back into shape.
Ray is so excited with his new garden bench! But it turns out finding the perfect spot for it is tricky, maybe a table would have been an easier fit!
Tá Chóilín agus Bhaibín ag dul amach anocht, dá bhrí sin tá Deaideó agus Muirisín ag tabhairt aire ar na páistí dóibh!
Tá folcadh I ndán do Smúirlín toisc go bhfuil boladh gránna ag teacht uaidh!
The Jitters: The semi -final. Sam, as captain, at last comes face to face with Ruby and the team must overcome their toughest challenge to date.
One step from Croker: Each is facing individual obstacles and trying to find a place in the world, but they all come together as a team on the hurling pitch.
The panda meets a shy penguin.
Wee Reg the puppy loves to wag his tail, though the one thing Wee Reg loves more than wagging his tail is helping his friends.
Reggie Plays Rough: While playing tag, Reggie becomes so engrossed in the game that he goes on a rampage! Upset by the chaos, Huey and the others declare that they don't want to play anymore.
Andy and the Manatee: Andy heads to the Caribbean in search of some seagrass he needs for a rescued manatee.
